text: My son brought me to enjoy the movie as a Mother's day gift.  The scenery and music were simply breathtaking and heart touching for me as a person who was born in China, and a mother who shares the feelings with the animal moms.  As I tried to hold back tears in multiple occasions during the movie, I couldn't help to think just how much we, human beings, have forgotten who we are on this planet.  We are no different then these beautiful and precious animals in term of lives.   We have the privilege to share all this wonderful planet has to offer, but have NO rights to make them hurt or suffer.  My respect and appreciation goes to those animal video photographers who dedicated so much to this movie.

text: BIG SPOILER! V V V The crew let the snow leopard mother die. Seemed like her two young ones probably died as well. That is not clear. It seemed the crew may have had some some subtle influence on events, and I think they might have had some responsibility for what happened. Certainly they stood by while the cat died, and then showed the corpse on the screen. If the cat couldn't hunt anymore, babies weren't going to survive. The snow leopard is in decline; these might have been captured and released or even placed in a (good) animal park. Beats starving to death. You have an opportunity to help, help.
